  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through a complex sequence of transactions. Typical legal definitions include:\n\n1. Basic components:\n- Concealing the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Transforming criminal proceeds into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Disguising the origin of money from criminal activities\n\n2. Common legal elements:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Knowing funds derive from criminal activity\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legal\n\n3. Key stages typically recognized:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (complex transactions to obscure origin)\n- Integration (reintroducing funds as seemingly legitimate income)\n\n4. Jurisdictional variations exist, but most definitions require:\n- Specific intent\n- Knowledge of criminal source\n- Deliberate financial manipulation\n\n5. Regulated under:\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- International financial crime statutes\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
